  "text": "In the following theorem we combine Diaconis and Saloff Coste's comparison method (Theorems 1 and 2) with upper bounds on mixing time (Theorem 7) and lower bounds on mixing time (Theorem 5) to obtain a comparison theorem for mixing times (Theorem 8). This combination was first provided by Randall and Tetali in Proposition 4 of [CITATION_1] . We use the same reasoning as Randall and Tetali, though we consider odd flows in order to avoid assuming that the eigenvalues are non-negative.",
